This paper is about a data analysis system that leverages distributed memory abstraction to provide a unified engine that can run SQL queries and sophisticated analytics functions at scale. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.DB (databases), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.SE (software engineering). However, given that the paper focuses on the performance and fault tolerance properties of the system, cs.DB and cs.DC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions iterative machine learning, which suggests that cs.LG is a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper discusses the system's execution engine and mid-query replanning, which could be relevant to cs.SE.
